I"B<p>For all the things you can buy online, I haven’t seen many sites selling raw diamonds, though there are many selling jewellery.</p>

<p>Me and my friend Bhavik were tasked with creating such twin websites. 
One site for selling certified diamonds. 
Each such diamond is certified by central authorities, and is expensive. 
Second site for selling parcel diamonds (aka loose diamonds). 
These diamonds are tiny, relatively cheap, bought in bulk and are typically used for creating jewellery.</p>

<figure>
    <a href="https://deepakvadgama.com/images/blog/sejalgems/sejalgems-home-1.png"><img src="https://deepakvadgama.com/images/blog/sejalgems/sejalgems-home-1.png" /></a>
</figure>

<figure>
    <a href="https://deepakvadgama.com/images/blog/sejalgems/sejalgems-twin-site.png"><img src="https://deepakvadgama.com/images/blog/sejalgems/sejalgems-twin-site.png" /></a>
</figure>

